Abstract = {{An imaginary dialogue between an ethnologist and an ethnomusicologist
   introduces readers to a debate about the underpinnings of activities in
   ethnomusicology and the latter's place among the human sciences. Can
   ethnomusicology be considered to be a full-fledged discipline ? Or
   should we see it as needing bridges toward other fields ? If so, which
   bridges, and under what conditions ? This attempt to answer these
