   learnt which team was better in each pair. The pairs of teams were
   adjacent members of a seven-term series of team rankings (A-G). The
   participants were not explicitly informed of this underlying stimulus
   hierarchy. Once a participant reached the training criterion, they were
   tested on the six training pairs and three novel pairs (BD, CE, and DF)
