   analyse. The stance he assumes vis-a-vis those women performers is,
   however, problematic: the essayist/narrator remains detached in the
   manner of a flaneur, who observes but remains passive. This becomes
   evident in an examination of Kracauer's narrative strategies in
   comparison with two short fictional texts, Robert Walser's `Ovation'
