   extending infinitely above the territorial space. Adopting the formal
   outline of a dislocated spiral, transparent shell-shaped structures are
   slung from pilotis. Spatiovore is a radical expression of the technical
   innovations of the period (tensile structures, hanging platforms,
   domes, etc.) combines into a comprehensive urban project.
   In 1965, Constant took up painting once again, via the intermediary of
   architectural drawing. Labyrinthine Space (1969) explores a
   situationist theme: that of ``non-space{''} suitable for the
   ``construction of situations{''} cultivated by homo ludens. Constant's
