Abstract = {{The main goal of this research was to investigate the effects of two
   factors on the construction of spatial representations : the modality
   of presentation of spatial information (Spatial configuration versus
   Text) and the type of organization of this information (Linear versus
   Non Linear). In a preliminary experiment, we examined the internal
   structure of subjects' descriptions of features of an imaginary island.
   The results showed that most subjects organized linearly their
   descriptions. We used these findings in our experiment investigating
   which conditions allow the construction of spatial representations.
   After learning the content of an imaginary island, subjects had to
   judge the location of the items they had learned previously. Following
   our hypotheses, the main results showed that the quality of the spatial
