   method. The respondents received a questionnaire with 12 pairs of
   scenarios, imaginary patient cases, each of which contained two to
   three different prioritization criteria (e.g., child, old patient, poor
   patient). Respondents were asked which one of each scenario pair they
   would choose ii only one patient could be treated. The scenarios were
   randomly put into 30 different questionnaire sets. There was a random
   selection of 241 doctors and 151 nurses in Finland, with response rates
   of 60.3\% and 50.3\%, respectively.
